explanation: This solution uses a single pass through the string, keeping track of the number of unmatched '(' characters. When a ')' is encountered, it either matches an existing '(' or requires an insertion. The final result is the sum of the number of unmatched ')' characters and the number of unmatched '(' characters, multiplied by 2.

